### Describe the bug

With a simple route parameter being `Guid[]`, routing fails validation and doesn't continue the method if more than one Guid is present in the request url.  Swagger sends the request as `https://{{BASEPATH}}/method/{GUID},{GUID}`, but the request fails validation.

### Expected Behavior

I should be able to receive an array of Guids as a route parameter. Or an error should show up saying that Guid[] parameters are not allowed.

### Steps To Reproduce

Use the following `ApiController` in a web api project: 

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;

namespace TestWebApi.Controllers;

[ApiController]
[Route("[controller]")]
public class TestController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly ILogger<TestController> _logger;

    public TestController(ILogger<TestController> logger)
    {
        _logger = logger;
    }

    [HttpGet("{guids}",Name = "GetWeatherForecast")]
    public IActionResult Get([FromRoute] Guid[] guids)
    {
        return Ok(new
        {
            Guids = guids,
        });
    }
}
```

Running swagger will show everything correctly and let you send any number of Guids as a comma separated list.  ASP.NET returns a 400 status with a message like: 

```json
